HEADWORD: Leavening
<hw>Leav"en*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of making light, or causing to ferment, by means of
leaven.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which leavens or makes light.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Leavenous</ent>⟦br⟧
